Reliability overhaul: fix load-twice, request state on boot, buildings grow

Root-cause pass on the recurring "had to load twice" + flaky upgrades:

- StadiumController: the building wiring checked Owner.Value the instant the
  ObjectValue replicated, but the *reference* resolves a beat later — so on a cold
  first load it read nil, bailed, and (being marked done) never retried. Now it
  WAITS for Owner.Value to resolve, only marks a model handled once it's sure, and
  RE-SCANS unwired buildings on every profile update so a race always self-heals.
  This is the fix for upgrades needing a second join.
- RequestState remote: client asks the server for its state once all handlers are
  connected (x3), so the HUD balance/income populate immediately instead of waiting
  for (or missing) the periodic push.
- PlotService: every non-stands building now visibly scales up with its level
  (re-seated on the ground), on both build and upgrade — upgrades finally feel
  visible, not "useless".
- Removed the green debug overlay (its job is done; data is confirmed flowing).

